                   <h1>
                       <span lang="EN-GB">Ministry of Trade and Investment Attracts N 4.29 trillion 
                       Investments in 6 months</span></h1>
                   <p class="MsoNormal">
                       &nbsp;</p>
                   <p>
                       <span lang="EN-GB">The Ministry of Trade and Investments has secured N 4.89 
                       trillion worth of investment commitments from local and international investors. 
                       This amount was secured after 60 meetings in a period of 6 months by the 
                       SegunAganga led ministry.</span></p>
                   <p>
                       <span lang="EN-GB">Local investors contributed N 2.67 trillion to the amount, 
                       whilst international investors contributed N 2.2 trillion.</span></p>
                   <p>
                       <span lang="EN-GB">Vulcan Energy, an American company plans to invest N 620 
                       billion in Nigeria’s oil and gas sector. Also Sinopec of China and Total plan to 
                       invest N 155 billion each in the country’s foremost economic sector.</span></p>
                   <p>
                       <span lang="EN-GB">According to Mr.Aganga, “The ministry has begun collaboration 
                       with the various companies, both local and foreign, to ensure that the 
                       investments are executed within the time-frame given, especially by ensuring 
                       that there are no bottlenecks in the way of smooth business for the operators.</span></p>
                   <p>
                       <span lang="EN-GB">“The commitments have been made on a win-win basis and in 
                       order to make sure that the projects are executed and Nigerians reap their 
                       benefits in the lifetime of this administration, we are attaching experts to the 
                       various companies to monitor and evaluate the projects as they progress.”</span></p>

